docs.abstract: For many members of the force, the decision to fire the officer whose chokehold led to Eric Garner’s death signaled a shift in the rules of engagement.
docs.snippet: For many members of the force, the decision to fire the officer whose chokehold led to Eric Garner’s death signaled a shift in the rules of engagement.
docs.lead_paragraph: The video of the final moments in the life of Eric Garner and his cries for help — “I can’t breathe” — ignited swift outrage, launching a campaign against aggressive policing and fueling the Black Lives Matter movement.

headline.main: After Pantaleo, Wary N.Y.P.D. Officers Say No One Has Their Backs
headline.print_headline: Police Department’s Rank and File Balk at Pantaleo’s Firing

docs.abstract: Trailing badly in the polls and in fund-raising for 2020, Mayor Bill de Blasio hopes that an hour on CNN Sunday before the nation’s voters can change his standing.
docs.snippet: Trailing badly in the polls and in fund-raising for 2020, Mayor Bill de Blasio hopes that an hour on CNN Sunday before the nation’s voters can change his standing.
docs.lead_paragraph: He’s entrenched toward the rear in fund-raising totals. He rejects the validity of the various polls showing him at zero percent.

headline.main: Inslee Out. Moulton Out. De Blasio? Town Hall May Be Last Gasp.

docs.abstract: The events ahead of the Bears-Packers regular season opener are the first since the N.F.L. formed a partnership with Jay-Z to co-produce the league’s entertainment and support a social activism campaign.
docs.snippet: The events ahead of the Bears-Packers regular season opener are the first since the N.F.L. formed a partnership with Jay-Z to co-produce the league’s entertainment and support a social activism campaign.
docs.lead_paragraph: Meek Mill, Rapsody and Meghan Trainor will perform on Thursday in Chicago before the N.F.L. opens its 100th season when the Bears host the Green Bay Packers. The artists, who were chosen over a period of months, are the first to perform at an N.F.L. event since the league formed a broad partnership this month with Jay-Z, who will help produce entertainment at the Super Bowl and other prominent N.F.L. events, and support the league’s social activism campaign, Inspire Change.

headline.main: N.F.L. Kickoff Event to Include Meek Mill
headline.print_headline: N.F.L. Kickoff Event Highlights Jay-Z Partnership

docs.abstract: A video appeared to show two officers punching an immobilized 62-year-old man, adding fuel to the recent anger over police conduct.
docs.snippet: A video appeared to show two officers punching an immobilized 62-year-old man, adding fuel to the recent anger over police conduct.
docs.lead_paragraph: HONG KONG — Two Hong Kong police officers were arrested on Tuesday after a video appeared to show them hitting a 62-year-old man in the genitals, stomach and face while he was strapped to a gurney in a hospital in June.

headline.main: Hong Kong Police Officers Arrested Over Beating of Man in Hospital

byline.original: By Daniel Victor and Katherine Li

docs.abstract: At a Beijing news conference, an official said China would “never allow any violent attempt to push Hong Kong into a dangerous situation.”
docs.snippet: At a Beijing news conference, an official said China would “never allow any violent attempt to push Hong Kong into a dangerous situation.”
docs.lead_paragraph: HONG KONG — An official in Beijing on Tuesday issued China’s sternest denunciation yet of the demonstrations in Hong Kong, saying they had “exceeded the scope of free assembly” and warning that the semiautonomous city would not be allowed to descend into chaos.

headline.main: China Warns Hong Kong Protesters Not to ‘Take Restraint for Weakness’
headline.print_headline: Beijing to Hong Kong: Don’t ‘Take Restraint for Weakness’

byline.original: By Austin Ramzy and Tiffany May

docs.abstract: Champ Bailey delivered an impassioned plea Saturday for a discussion on race. Others have found more subtle ways to bring social justice and player health issues to the fore.
docs.snippet: Champ Bailey delivered an impassioned plea Saturday for a discussion on race. Others have found more subtle ways to bring social justice and player health issues to the fore.
docs.lead_paragraph: On Saturday, Champ Bailey, who was one of eight former players and league executives inducted into the Pro Football Hall of Fame this weekend, devoted part of his nationally televised speech to urge white Americans to pay attention to the injustices black Americans face.

headline.main: Pro Football Hall of Fame Inductees Bring Causes to Canton

docs.abstract: A struggle in California, one of three states creating K-12 ethnic studies materials, highlights some of the fraught questions around the discipline.
docs.snippet: A struggle in California, one of three states creating K-12 ethnic studies materials, highlights some of the fraught questions around the discipline.
docs.lead_paragraph: Discuss a recent instance of police brutality in your community. Read op-eds arguing for and against legal status for unauthorized immigrants. Compare and contrast border conditions in the Palestinian territories and Mexico.

docs.abstract: The suspect’s mother called the police about a gun her son had ordered. Her lawyer said that it was an “informational call” and that she did not raise concerns he was a threat.
docs.snippet: The suspect’s mother called the police about a gun her son had ordered. Her lawyer said that it was an “informational call” and that she did not raise concerns he was a threat.
docs.lead_paragraph: ALLEN, Tex. — In the weeks before a gunman killed 22 people in a devastating rampage at an El Paso Walmart, the suspect’s mother called the police concerned about whether her 21-year-old son was mature or experienced enough for the powerful AK-style rifle he had ordered.

headline.main: El Paso Suspect Ordered Gun and Moved Out in Weeks Before Attack
headline.print_headline: Suspect Had Ordered Gun and Moved Out in Weeks Before Attack

byline.original: By Jack Healy and Sarah Mervosh

docs.abstract: The police commissioner sent a valuable message by firing the New York City officer who put Mr. Garner in a chokehold that turned fatal.
docs.snippet: The police commissioner sent a valuable message by firing the New York City officer who put Mr. Garner in a chokehold that turned fatal.
docs.lead_paragraph: As he announced that he was firing the police officer who had put Eric Garner in the chokehold that led to his death, New York City’s police commissioner, James O’Neill, sent the country’s largest police force a message: You may not think I’m on your side, but I am.

headline.main: A Measure of Justice for Eric Garner, and for Daniel Pantaleo
headline.print_headline: A Measure of Justice for Eric Garner
